it's not in competition with Narwhals at all. In fact, Narwhals supports IBIS as an input.

00:22:37.280 --> 00:22:43.280
So you can choose to use IBIS with a Narwhals front end if you wish to.

00:22:44.079 --> 00:22:50.079
Yeah, I don't think, I don't regard the projects as competitors, but I agree that to an onlooker

00:22:50.079 --> 00:22:59.439
who isn't familiar with, isn't enmeshed in this ecosystem that superficially, when you squint,

00:23:00.959 --> 00:23:05.599
you squint at these projects from afar, they do look very similar. But when you actually get

00:23:05.599 --> 00:23:13.280
involved in the details, there's what it feels like to actually use the library day to day.

00:23:13.280 --> 00:23:17.920
