started with the project? Yes, I've covered the motivation, which was about not having

00:28:17.680 --> 00:28:23.119
data science tools all locked into Pandas, and about physically how it started. I just put it

00:28:23.119 --> 00:28:31.040
out there. I remember sending it to some newsletters, and to my surprise, people started

00:28:32.959 --> 00:28:40.800
checking out the repository, giving it stars. And I got a bit of a signal that, okay, maybe it

00:28:40.800 --> 00:28:47.280
can be useful. Maybe people like the idea. And the original name for the project was Polars API

00:28:47.280 --> 00:28:52.959
Compat. The idea was that it would just make other APIs compatible with the Polars API.

00:28:53.680 --> 00:28:56.560
And then I figured, wait a second, I really want this to become popular.

00:28:58.000 --> 00:29:01.839
